	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I don't see a Samus likeness at all. The slighlty footballish helmet shape is unique enough to give a strong silhouette, and I prefer it to the post-Samus-comparison alternative that you posted more recently.<br /><br />For the idle stances, I like the idea of two sets of animation, but they are too similar to pull off the &quot;in danger&quot; and &quot;not in danger&quot;. Perhaps for the in-danger: legs wider apart, arms out, looking more ready for danger. I think somewhat stronger, exaggerated gesture and body language would be vital for conveying information at that size.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
